+# SCC Test Suite
+
+Three-layer smoke verification for the SCC vision-token compression feature.
+Formal unit tests live under `tests/ut`; use this directory when you want
+manual wiring checks or an end-to-end server smoke.
+
+| Layer | Runtime | Needs vLLM server? | Needs NPU? | What it proves |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| 1 -- algorithm | ~1 s | no | no | `scc_compress_to_target` math is correct |
+| 2 -- patch wiring | ~5-30 s | no | no (import-only) | env vars parse, monkey-patch applies |
+| 3 -- end-to-end | ~1-2 min | **yes** (running server) | yes | a real request triggers the SCC path |
+
+## Unit Tests
+
+```bash
+pytest tests/ut/ops/test_scc_compressor.py
+pytest tests/ut/patch/platform/test_patch_engine_core_scc.py
+```
+
+## Files
+
+```
+tests/scc/
+├── README.md                     (this file)
+├── test_layer1_algorithm.py      CPU-only, no vLLM
+├── test_layer2_patch.py          imports vllm, does not start server
+├── curl_smoke.sh                 one POST to /v1/chat/completions
+└── collect_env.sh                environment debugging utility
+```
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+```bash
+conda activate vllm-ascend
+# Confirm the package is findable
+python -c "import vllm_ascend, vllm; print(vllm_ascend.__file__); print(vllm.__version__)"
+```
+
+## Layer 1 -- Algorithm
+
+```bash
+python tests/scc/test_layer1_algorithm.py
+```
+
+**Expect:** `Layer 1: all tests passed.`
+
+**If it fails:** The bug is in `vllm_ascend/ops/scc_compressor.py`. Fix it
+there; don't touch the patch file or the server.
+
+## Layer 2 -- Patch Registration
+
+Run both the enabled and disabled paths (separate invocations, because the
+enable flag is read on import and caching matters):
+
+```bash
+# Enable path
+VLLM_ASCEND_ENABLE_SCC=1 VLLM_ASCEND_SCC_RATIO=0.3 \
+  python tests/scc/test_layer2_patch.py
+
+# Disable path
+VLLM_ASCEND_ENABLE_SCC=0 python tests/scc/test_layer2_patch.py
+```
+
+**Expect:** `Layer 2: all tests passed.` for both.
+
+**Common failures & fixes:**
+
+| Failure | Likely cause |
+|---|---|
+| `VLLM_ASCEND_ENABLE_SCC expected True, got False` | `envs.py` entry is missing or typo'd |
+| `ImportError: patch_qwen25vl_scc` | Worker entry point not installed on the server |
+| `_scc_patched is missing` | `patch/platform/__init__.py` or `patch/worker/__init__.py` missing the SCC import line; OR `apply_qwen25vl_scc_patch()` is short-circuiting (check guards) |
+| `get_num_image_tokens still points at upstream` | `_scc_patched` got set but the rebinding was skipped |
+| `SCC is disabled but patch still marked target class` | Disable branch is broken in `apply_qwen25vl_scc_patch()` |
+
+## Layer 3 -- End-to-End Smoke
+
+```bash
+# Terminal 1: start the server with SCC enabled
+VLLM_ASCEND_ENABLE_SCC=1 bash start_vllm_server.sh
+
+# Terminal 2: wait for "Uvicorn running on http://..." then run:
+bash tests/scc/curl_smoke.sh
+```
+
+**Expect in Terminal 1's log:**
+
+1. Startup banner (proves patch module was imported):
+   ```
+   [SCC] Qwen2.5-VL vision-token compression ENABLED (ratio=0.3, tau=0.95, epsilon=0.05).
+   ```
+2. Placeholder shrink (proves processor-side patch fires):
+   ```
+   [SCC] shrink prompt placeholders: N=... -> K=...
+   ```
+3. ViT-output compression (proves model-side patch fires):
+   ```
+   [SCC] compress ViT out: ... -> ...
+   ```
+
+**Diagnosing partial output:**
+
+| What you see | What's broken |
+|---|---|
+| Nothing starting with `[SCC]` | Patch module not imported. Layer 2 regressed; fix there first. |
+| Only line (1) | Patch loaded but neither method was actually called. Qwen2.5-VL class name / import path changed in this vLLM version. |
+| (1) + (2) only | Processor-side OK, model-side failed. `_process_image_input` / `_process_video_input` names moved in `Qwen2_5_VLForConditionalGeneration`. |
+| (1) + (3) only | Model-side OK, processor-side failed. `Qwen2VLProcessingInfo.get_num_*` rename; placeholder count will mismatch K. |
+| All three | SCC is end-to-end wired. Proceed to real evaluation. |
+
+## Tips
+
+- Layer 3's `curl_smoke.sh` sends a 1x1 PNG. That's enough to trigger the
+  ViT; you don't need real video frames.
+- If you change `scc_compressor.py`, re-run `tests/ut/ops/test_scc_compressor.py`
+  and Layer 1. If you change `patch_engine_core_scc.py` or
+  `patch_qwen25vl_scc.py`, re-run `tests/ut/patch/platform/test_patch_engine_core_scc.py`
+  and Layer 2. Only if both pass
+  should you pay the cost of Layer 3.
+- No need to rebuild the C++ extension after editing these Python files.
+  SCC is all Python.
+
+## Environment Debugging
+
+```bash
+bash tests/scc/collect_env.sh > /tmp/env.txt 2>&1
+```
+
+This captures OS, CANN, NPU, Python, and vllm-ascend versions for bug reports.
